data.title: My Novel or Varieties in English Life by Pisistratus Caxton by Sir Edward Bulwer Lytton
data.meta_description: New York: Cassell Publishing Co., 1890. Hardcover. 486 p., frontispiece; 19 cm. Maroon cloth with gilt-stamped spine title. No date of publication. The Cassell Publishing Co. existed from 1890 to 1893. Decorated endpapers. First published in 1853, this novel by prolific English writer Sir Edward Bulwer-Lytton presents English life of the first half of the 19th century in London and the village Hazeldean. A scarce edition. In Very Good+ Condition: edges
